headline: Microsoft’s AI Growth Story Tests Investor Patience On Heavy Spending
summary: Microsoft (NasdaqGS:MSFT) reported second quarter results with record cloud and AI revenues and the launch of its Maia 200 AI chip. The company highlighted strong AI related customer commitments, including from OpenAI, contributing to a growing business backlog. Despite beating earnings expectations, Microsoft shares saw their steepest single day decline since 2020 as investors focused on heavy AI infrastructure spending and slower Azure growth.
